# prose_translation = And one must resolve the difficulties that relate to the diction, for example, by a gloss— "first upon the mules": for perhaps he is not speaking of the half-donkeys but of the guards. And in the case of Dolon, "who in truth was evil in form": not ill-proportioned in body but ugly in face, for the Cretans call the well-formed "the fair-of-face." And "mix it rather stronger" does not mean unmixed, as for drunkards, but rather quicker.
# literal_translation = The but to the [matters] relating to diction one must resolve, for instance by a gloss the [phrase] "the mules first": for perhaps not the half-donkeys he says but the guards. And the [case] of Dolon, "who indeed in form was bad," not the body ill-proportioned but the face ugly; for the well-formed the Cretans the fair-of-face call. And the [phrase] "mix it rather stronger" not the unmixed as for drunkards but the quicker.
